will change California's
emissions for the year,
substantially.

43:53.264 --> 43:58.569 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CAT WISE: Steve Conley an
atmospheric scientist
with the University of
California, Davis,

43:58.603 --> 44:03.474 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
