gas, is the main component of
natural gas.

44:19.156 --> 44:24.362 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's extremely potent. It's
more efficient
at trapping radiation and heat
than carbon

44:24.395 --> 44:26.130 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
dioxide.

44:26.163 --> 44:31.469 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEVE CONLEY: That first flight,
we measured
something like 44,000 kilograms
per hour.

44:31.502 --> 44:36.207 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The best number that I have come
up with to
give people a perspective, it's
close to 100,000

44:36.240 --> 44:40.177 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
